The paper discusses the use of feature selection for detecting DDoS attacks in cloud computing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of machine learning algorithms for classification and detection suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on cloud computing and distributed systems suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE).
